This script installs various software on a Linux machine using different installation methods. It installs the following software:

Visual Studio Code
Jira
GameMaker Studio
Android Studio
Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and Sketch
Wwise
Asana
Google Analytics
Microsoft Azure CLI
Ansible
Terraform
Docker
Kubernetes
Prometheus
Prerequisites
Before running this script, ensure that you have a Linux machine with root access.

Usage
Perform the following steps to install the software:

Open a terminal window on your Linux machine.

Copy the script to your terminal window.

Run the script using the following command:

sudo bash script_name.sh
Replace script_name.sh with the name of the script file.

Wait for the script to complete. The script will install all the software listed above.

Conclusion
By following the above steps, you should now have all the software installed on your Linux machine.
If you encounter any issues during the installation process,
consult the documentation for each tool or seek assistance from a Linux administrator or support community.
